      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TRENTINO (8) made light work of the tricky draw with a fast early sectional but gathered in and had to settle for the minors, finishing third (18.16) at this track over 305m. Form from his last run is proving to be solid. Key chance in this line up. COMPTON SHELLY (1) is a quick dog who thrives over the short dashes. Found it a bit far latest when finished fifth over 455m at Murray Bridge (26.39) in a Grade 6 but is better suited back in trip here. Has a strong winning record here at the trip including two wins. The form from her last run stacks up well. Has ability and can measure up. COMPTON LIZZIE (6) has a strong overall record having five wins and eight places from 17 starts including a last start third (30.63) over 512m at this track. Solid record here winning three races. Looks well placed here and has the ability. Go well. OLLIE DEEDS (4) is worth consideration after filling a hole last start.",
